default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPhilip Morris International Inc. (“PMI”) is the
default&#xa0;
defaultleading international tobacco company.  
defaultIts
default products
default which include the 
defaultworld’s number one cigarette brand Marlboro
default 
defaultare
default sold in
default&#xa0;
defaultmore 
defaultthan 180 countries.  PMI operates in the UK and Ireland through its subsidiary Philip Morris Lim
defaultited (“PML”)
default.
default&#xa0;
default2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultF
defaultighting the illicit trade in tobacco is a top priority for PML.  
defaultWe invest significant resources in combating the illicit trade, and cooperate with government and law enforcement at every level, both in the UK and internationally.  
default&#xa0;
default3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAlthough the UK’s legal framework provides adequate penalties for tobacco smuggling, deterrence is weakened by the difficulty of detection, and relatively 
defaultlow tariffs linked to current sentencing guidelines.
default&#xa0;
default4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSmuggling
default and the illicit
default 
defaulttrade 
defaulttakes different forms
default:
default&#xa0;
defaultCigarettes bearing trademarks that 
defaultare
default manufactured without the 
defaulttrademark owner
default’s
default permission.
defaultCigarettes that enter or are sold in a market in violation of fiscal/custom
defaults
default laws.
defaultCigarettes that are produced in one market and primarily smuggled into and sold in another where they have no legal distribution.
default5.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIt 
defaultrange
defaults
default 
defaultfrom small scale smuggling (often involving criminals gangs), colloquially known as ‘ant smuggling’, to large container shipments involving organised crime.  Both the UK and Ireland face similar problems shaped by common drivers of supply and demand.  Irish ports are seen as a ‘back door’ to the UK and the illicit trade is frequently linked to paramilitary groups in Northern Ireland.  
default&#xa0;
default6.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultT
defaulthe UK and Irish illicit markets are
default 
defaultintricately linked
default.  
defaultAs
default plain packaging
default 
defaultinevitably increases the ease of supply of illicit tobacco, the prospect of Ireland introducing this policy will inevitably impact the UK. 
default&#xa0;
defaultRecommendations
default7.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe UK should continue to invest in combating the illicit trade, with dedicated funding todefault helpdefault facilitate defaultco-ordination across law enforcement agencies. default&#xa0;
default8.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLaw enforcement needs a co-ordinated defaultmulti-agency defaultapproach to deterring defaultsmall scaledefault smugglingdefault.  This includes greater focus on preventing illicit tobacco entering the UK, more effort to disrupt inland distribution networks, and heavier penalties
default, including aggressive pursuit of asset forfeiture opportunities,
default when offenders are identified.
default  More generally the Government should consider whether current penalties provide significant deterrence.
default&#xa0;
default9.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe Government should defaultprioritisedefault tackling the problem defaultofdefault factories in overseas free trade zones where local oversight is lax.default  
defaultThese are frequently located in
default jurisdictions with which the UK and EU enjoy
default close ties, but provide a key source for 
defaultorganised crime
default groups
default 
defaultincluding
default paramilitaries. 
default Political engagement by senior levels of government and efforts to leverage EU influence 
defaultwould complement the successes of HMRC’s overseas network of Fiscal Crime Liaison Officers. 
default&#xa0;default10.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe UK must defaultpreparedefault a strategy to adapt to changes in the illicit trade arising from the Irish Government’s proposed introduction of plain packaging.default  
defaultThis would include even closer cooperation between UK and Irish law enforcement agencies.  
defaultThe illicit markets of both countries are closely related, and since plain packaging is highly likely to increase the supply of illicit tobacco into Ireland, the policy will inevitably impact the UK (in the same way that its introduction in Scotland would impact England and Wales).  
default&#xa0;
default11.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultFinally, the UK should limit further tax increases to inflation, and avoid any sudden or excessive rises.default  The UK (with Ireland) has the highest tobacco taxes in the EU.  Consumers’ resistance to ever higher taxes and their willingness to switch to easily available alternatives that are unlicensed, unregulated and untaxed lie at the heart of this problem.
