default17.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPMI works closely with European authorities.  PMI signed a
default Cooperation agreement with the European Commission in 2004, to which the UK, Ireland and 
defaultall other Member States are also party.
default  
defaultThe agreement established regular exchanges of
default information between PMI, OLAF
default and the Member States regarding seizures of counterfeit and genuine cigarettes.  
defaultThis information 
defaultunderpins
default Project Star, an annual EU wide study of tobacco consumption that PMI commissions from KPMG
default.
default 
defaultThe results
default 
defaultare
default presented to both OLAF and representatives of all 
defaultEU
default Member States
default and 
defaultallows PMI and law enforcement to identify 
defaultEU
default wide trends more quickly. 
defaultThe 
defaultCooperation
default agreement also established
default a range of supply chain control measures 
defaultincluding enhanced ‘Know Your Customer’ checks, sales volume monitoring, and tracking and tracing obligations
default.
default&#xa0;
default18.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn the UK PM
defaultL
default participates with the rest of the industry and HMRC in an anti-illicit trade working group,
default 
defaultand also invests significant resources in commissioning research and gathering intelligence on the nature and extent of the illicit trade
default.  PMI, along with other industry players, is party to an Intelligence Sharing Protocol with HMRC (with extensive intelligence sharing with HMRC’s FCLO network) and further work is continuing on finalising a broader MOU between HMRC and industry participants.
