defaultThe possible impact of standardiseddefault (or plain)default packaging in Ireland on the quantity and availability of illegal tobacco in the UKdefault34.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPlain packaging risks fuelling the illicit tobacco trade, as 24 former senior police officers in the UK have warned.
default  Given that large scale smugglers view the UK and Ireland as a single market,
default any increase in the supply of illicit tobacco to Ireland will inevitably flow through to the British mainland. 
default&#xa0;
default35.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPlain packaging 
defaultfuels
default the illicit trade in three ways.
default  First, demand for 
defaultbranded 
defaultcontraband will increase. 
default 
defaultIntroducing plain packaging will not erase branded tobacco, it will just hand a monopoly to criminals who already provide a cheaper product.
default&#xa0;
default36.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSecond, it will facilitate counterfeiting, as 
defaultmultiple 
defaultexperts have warned.
default  Economies of scale make it cheaper for counterfeiters to imitate a single plain packet design than multiple different brands.  
default&#xa0;
default37.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThird, by removing branding, 
defaultthe policy will weaken brand loyalty and hasten
default the current trend towards down-trading
default.   Ma
defaultking tobacco a commoditi
defaults
defaulted product with compet
defaultition based purely around price 
defaultwill play into the hands of 
defaultorganised criminals.
default 
default L
defaultegitimate brands will not
default be able to compete on price
default 
defaultagainst
default untaxed and unregulated i
defaultllicit whites
default.
default&#xa0;
default38.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIllicit whites are already a major and fast-growing problem, attracting
default the most
default price-sensitive smokers.  
defaultAn empty pack survey in Q4 2011 found 68 different illicit white brands in the UK, but over 450 have been identified worldwide.
default  Popular demand is proven: p
defaultlain packaging will
default make Ireland (and the UK) a target for increased supply
default. 
default 
default 
default 
defaultAlready ‘baggies’
default (illicit unbranded cigarettes sold cheaply in sealed transparent plastic bags) 
defaultand unbranded loose tobacco are 
defaultcommon in many countries. 
default The situation
default in the UK and Ireland could easily deteriorate further.
default 
default&#xa0;
default39.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultI
defaultf, as anticipated, plain packaging leads to price reductions and therefore increases in tobacco excise to compensate, the price difference between the legal and illicit products will increase. This will increase the profit for tobacco smugglers and further incentivize them to target the Irish market.  For the reasons discussed above, any increase in supply to Ireland will flow through to the UK.
